        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer77193285" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6254690473416805433">This book is a collection of twelve stories starring the priest, Father Brown and his friend Inspector Flambeau written in the first half of the twentieth century. Father Brown solves things by observation and thought, in some ways like Poirot, but in an unassuming and modest manner. The stories are each very different, but are very good reading. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


