<span id="freeTextContainer15421600166821618689">I started off liking these humorous crime tales, very accessible despite their antiquity. But the stories became less entertaining, the more of them that I read. As more horrific racial stereotypes (surely &quot;of their time, but no more repulsive for that) were introduced, I found myself skipping whole pages in an effort to escape. Not the best sign. I&apos;m fairly sure I&apos;ve heard some of these serialised on the radio, and for me that&apos;s probably a better medium - idly listening to the better ones, whil</span>
  <span id="freeText15421600166821618689" style="display:none">I started off liking these humorous crime tales, very accessible despite their antiquity. But the stories became less entertaining, the more of them that I read. As more horrific racial stereotypes (surely "of their time, but no more repulsive for that) were introduced, I found myself skipping whole pages in an effort to escape. Not the best sign. I'm fairly sure I've heard some of these serialised on the radio, and for me that's probably a better medium - idly listening to the better ones, whilst getting on with something else.</span>
